    "C PRELIMINARIES C.1 Problem SetupIn the discrete VLN task, an agent is initialized at a starting node and needs to explore the navigation connectivity graph G = (V, E) to reach a target node, following a language instruction I. V and E represent the nodes and edges in the navigation connectivity graph.At each timestep t, the agent receives a panoramic observation O t of its current node.",
    "O t composed of N o single-view observations O t,n, i.e., O t = {O t,n } No n=1.",
    "Each O t,n contains an RGB image B t,n and the directional information.",
    "With the instructions I and current visual observations O t, the agent infers the action a t for each step t from the candidate navigable views N (O t) ∈ O t, which corresponds to the neighbor nodes of the current node.In this paper, we propose to cast VLN as an open-world landmark discovery problem to introduce large models for assisting VLN tasks.",
    "We define the problem in the following."
  ]
